<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="56" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1345,1548]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,243,1345,1367]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gali, R. Pacifico &amp; Almeda" authorityYear="2022" box="[267,497,1346,1367]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macaubensis">
<emphasis box="[267,497,1346,1367]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">Microlicia macaubensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by its sessile leaves 
<quantity box="[871,979,1346,1368]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="7.8" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.6">5.6–10 mm</quantity>
long, margin sparsely ciliate with 1–4 eglandular trichomes 
<quantity box="[293,393,1382,1403]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="0.65" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.3">0.3–1 mm</quantity>
long or glabrescent (these trichomes deciduous), both surfaces glandular-punctate, 1-nerved with the vein impressed on adaxial surface and slightly canaliculate on abaxial surface, yellow petals and dimorphic stamens with tetrasporangiate thecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
